HEADWORD: Ascariasis
<hw>As`ca*ri"a*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ an intestinal worm.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease,
usually accompanied by colicky pains and diarrhea, caused by the
presence of ascarids in the gastrointestinal canal.</def>⟦br⟧
